"""
MCP Bridge — Cross-Machine Tool & Skill Execution
==================================================
Proxies MCP tool calls and skill execution to remote peers (e.g., Forge).

Architecture:
    Wizard MCP Client
           │
           ▼
    Wizard Snackbar (/v1/mcp/bridge/call)
           │
           ├── Local MCP tools (direct)
           │
           └── Forge Snackmachine (file-based JSONL queue)
                     │
                     └── Forge local execution (spices/skills)

Transport backends:
  - HTTP:   POST /v1/mcp/call on remote Snackbar (for future HTTP peers)
  - File:   JSONL queue → Snackmachine commands.jsonl → replies.jsonl
  - SSH:    (future) direct SSH command execution

Usage:
    from mcp_bridge import MCPBridge
    bridge = MCPBridge()
    result = await bridge.call_tool("forge", "copernicus.search", {"query": "test"})
"""


